cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with facial landmark localisation using a feature extraction scheme and a cascaded shape regression framework. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a training sample augmentation scheme to improve model performance. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with automated facial landmark localisation. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with localisation of facial landmarks in images. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as the paper uses a cascaded shape regression framework which involves training a series of neural networks.
